I will give you a Coq proof state, including both hypotheses and a specific goal and your need to prove it. Your response should be a singular code block of Coq proof starting with "```coq
", ending with "Qed.```", without any additional explanation or commentary. Follow to these guidelines:
Introduce variables using unique names to avoid any conflicts.
Keep each command distinct and separated, avoid concatenations like ';' or '[cmd|cmd]'.
Organize your proof with bullets like '-', '+', and '*' instead of braces ({, }). Shift to their double symbols like '--' and '++', when necessary.
Effectively use given premises, follow the syntax and structure demonstrated in the examples provided.

Example 1:

Hypotheses:
n, m: nat
IHn: m + n = n + m

Goal:
m + S n = S n + m

Your Response:
```coq
simpl. rewrite <- IHn. auto.
Qed.```

Example 2:
Hypotheses:

Goal:
forall n m : nat, m + n = n + m

Your Response:
```coq
intros n m. induction n.
- simpl. auto.
- simpl. rewrite <- IHn. auto.
Qed.```

Solve This Proof State:

Hypotheses:
None

Goal:
forall kappa lambda : Cardinal, le_cardinal kappa lambda \/ le_cardinal lambda kappa

Premises:
Inductive le_cardinal : Cardinal -> Cardinal -> Prop := inj_le_cardinal : forall (X Y : Type) (f : X -> Y), injective f -> le_cardinal (cardinality X) (cardinality Y) Arguments inj_le_cardinal {X Y}%type_scope _%function_scope
Inductive Cardinal : Type := cardinality : Type -> Cardinal Arguments cardinality _%type_scope
le_cardinal_antisym : forall kappa lambda : Cardinal, le_cardinal kappa lambda -> le_cardinal lambda kappa -> eq_cardinal kappa lambda
eq_cardinal_impl_le_cardinal : forall kappa lambda : Cardinal, eq_cardinal kappa lambda -> le_cardinal kappa lambda
lt_cardinal = fun kappa lambda : Cardinal => le_cardinal kappa lambda /\ ~ eq_cardinal kappa lambda : Cardinal -> Cardinal -> Prop
cardinals_unbounded : forall kappa : Cardinal, exists lambda : Cardinal, gt_cardinal lambda kappa
ge_cardinal = fun kappa lambda : Cardinal => le_cardinal lambda kappa : Cardinal -> Cardinal -> Prop
gt_cardinal = fun kappa lambda : Cardinal => lt_cardinal lambda kappa : Cardinal -> Cardinal -> Prop
le_cardinal_ind : forall P : Cardinal -> Cardinal -> Prop, (forall (X Y : Type) (f : X -> Y), injective f -> P (cardinality X) (cardinality Y)) -> forall c c0 : Cardinal, le_cardinal c c0 -> P c c0
le_cardinal_sind : forall P : Cardinal -> Cardinal -> SProp, (forall (X Y : Type) (f : X -> Y), injective f -> P (cardinality X) (cardinality Y)) -> forall c c0 : Cardinal, le_cardinal c c0 -> P c c0
inj_le_cardinal : forall f : ?X -> ?Y, injective f -> le_cardinal (cardinality ?X) (cardinality ?Y) where ?X : [ |- Type] ?Y : [ |- Type]
surj_le_cardinal : forall f : ?X -> ?Y, surjective f -> le_cardinal (cardinality ?Y) (cardinality ?X) where ?X : [ |- Type] ?Y : [ |- Type]
le_cardinal_preorder = {| preord_refl := fun x : Cardinal => eq_cardinal_impl_le_cardinal x x (equiv_refl eq_cardinal_equiv x); preord_trans := fun (x y z : Cardinal) (H : le_cardinal x y) (H0 : le_cardinal y z) => match H in (le_cardinal c c0) return (le_cardinal c0 z -> le_cardinal c z) with | @inj_le_cardinal X Y f H1 => fun H2 : le_cardinal (cardinality Y) z => let H3 : cardinality Y = cardinality Y -> z = z -> le_cardinal (cardinality X) z := match H2 in (le_cardinal c c0) return (c = cardinality Y -> c0 = z -> le_cardinal (cardinality X) z) with | @inj_le_cardinal X0 Y0 f0 H3 => fun (H4 : cardinality X0 = cardinality Y) (H5 : cardinality Y0 = z)...
Cardinal_rect : forall P : Cardinal -> Type, (forall T : Type, P (cardinality T)) -> forall c : Cardinal, P c
Cardinal_ind : forall P : Cardinal -> Prop, (forall T : Type, P (cardinality T)) -> forall c : Cardinal, P c
Cardinal_sind : forall P : Cardinal -> SProp, (forall T : Type, P (cardinality T)) -> forall c : Cardinal, P c
Cardinal_rec : forall P : Cardinal -> Set, (forall T : Type, P (cardinality T)) -> forall c : Cardinal, P c
BinNat.N.le_ge_cases : forall n m : BinNums.N, BinNat.N.le n m \/ BinNat.N.le m n
BinInt.Z.le_gt_cases : forall n m : BinNums.Z, BinInt.Z.le n m \/ BinInt.Z.lt m n
BinNat.N.le_gt_cases : forall n m : BinNums.N, BinNat.N.le n m \/ BinNat.N.lt m n
BinInt.Z.le_ge_cases : forall n m : BinNums.Z, BinInt.Z.le n m \/ BinInt.Z.le m n
BinNat.N.lt_eq_cases : forall n m : BinNums.N, BinNat.N.le n m < -> BinNat.N.lt n m \/ n = m
BinInt.Z.sgn_spec : forall n : BinNums.Z, BinInt.Z.lt BinNums.Z0 n /\ BinInt.Z.sgn n = BinNums.Zpos BinNums.xH \/ BinNums.Z0 = n /\ BinInt.Z.sgn n = BinNums.Z0 \/ BinInt.Z.lt n BinNums.Z0 /\ BinInt.Z.sgn n = BinInt.Z.opp (BinNums.Zpos BinNums.xH)
BinNat.N.eq_mul_0 : forall n m : BinNums.N, BinNat.N.mul n m = BinNums.N0 < -> n = BinNums.N0 \/ m = BinNums.N0
BinNat.N.sqrt_up_succ_or : forall a : BinNums.N, BinNat.N.le BinNums.N0 a -> BinNat.N.sqrt_up (BinNat.N.succ a) = BinNat.N.succ (BinNat.N.sqrt_up a) \/ BinNat.N.sqrt_up (BinNat.N.succ a) = BinNat.N.sqrt_up a
eq_cardinal_sind : forall P : Cardinal -> Cardinal -> SProp, (forall (X Y : Type) (f : X -> Y), bijective f -> P (cardinality X) (cardinality Y)) -> forall c c0 : Cardinal, eq_cardinal c c0 -> P c c0
eq_cardinal_ind : forall P : Cardinal -> Cardinal -> Prop, (forall (X Y : Type) (f : X -> Y), bijective f -> P (cardinality X) (cardinality Y)) -> forall c c0 : Cardinal, eq_cardinal c c0 -> P c c0
BinInt.Z.div_unique : forall a b q r : BinNums.Z, BinInt.Z.le BinNums.Z0 r /\ BinInt.Z.lt r b \/ BinInt.Z.lt b r /\ BinInt.Z.le r BinNums.Z0 -> a = BinInt.Z.add (BinInt.Z.mul b q) r -> q = BinInt.Z.div a b
Record SOR (R : Type) (rO rI : R) (rplus rtimes rminus : R -> R -> R) (ropp : R -> R) (req rle rlt : R -> R -> Prop) : Prop := mk_SOR_theory { SORsetoid : Setoid.Setoid_Theory R req; SORplus_wd : forall x1 x2 : R, req x1 x2 -> forall y1 y2 : R, req y1 y2 ->...-> rlt rO (rtimes n m); SORneq_0_1 : ~ req rO rI } Arguments OrderedRing.SOR [R]%type_scope _ _ (_ _ _ _ _ _ _)%function_scope Arguments OrderedRing.mk_SOR_theory [R]%type_scope [rO rI] [rplus rtimes rminus ropp req]%function_scope (_ _)%function_scope _ (_ _ _ _ _)%function_scope _ (_ _ _ _ _ _ _)%function_scope
identity_rect_r : forall (A : Type) (a : A) (P : A -> Type), P a -> forall y : A, identity y a -> P y
BinNat.N.central_induction : forall A : BinNums.N -> Prop, Morphisms.Proper (Morphisms.respectful eq iff) A -> forall z : BinNums.N, A z -> (forall n : BinNums.N, A n <-> A (BinNat.N.succ n)) -> forall n : BinNums.N, A n
